M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: HIGH**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Fundamental patterns for structuring components to avoid prop
M|vercel-composition-patterns|proliferation and enable flexible composition.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: CRITICAL (prevents unmaintainable component variants)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Don't add boolean props like `isThread`, `isEditing`, `isDMThread` to customize
M|vercel-composition-patterns|component behavior. Each boolean doubles possible states and creates
M|vercel-composition-patterns|unmaintainable conditional logic. Use composition instead.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: boolean props create exponential complexity**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function Composer({
M|vercel-composition-patterns|onSubmit,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isThread,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|channelId,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isDMThread,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|dmId,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isEditing,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isForwarding,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}: Props) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Header />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{isDMThread ? (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<AlsoSendToDMField id={dmId} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|) : isThread ? (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|) : null}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{isEditing ? (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<EditActions />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|) : isForwarding ? (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardActions />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|) : (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<DefaultActions />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Footer onSubmit={onSubmit} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: composition eliminates conditionals**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Channel composer
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelComposer() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Header />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Attachments />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Thread composer - adds "also send to channel" field
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ThreadComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Header />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Edit composer - different footer actions
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function EditComposer() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Each variant is explicit about what it renders. We can share internals without
M|vercel-composition-patterns|sharing a single monolithic parent.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: HIGH (enables flexible composition without prop drilling)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Structure complex components as compound components with a shared ctx. Each
M|vercel-composition-patterns|subcomponent accesses shared state via ctx, not props. Consumers compose the
M|vercel-composition-patterns|pieces they need.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: monolithic component with render props**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function Composer({
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderHeader,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderFooter,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderActions,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|showAttachments,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|showFormatting,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|showEmojis,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}: Props) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderHeader?.()}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{showAttachments && <Attachments />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderFooter ? (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderFooter()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|) : (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{showFormatting && <Formatting />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{showEmojis && <Emojis />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderActions?.()}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: compound components with shared ctx**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue | null>(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerProvider({ children, state, actions, meta }: ProviderProps) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ComposerContext value={{ state, actions, meta }}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ComposerContext>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerFrame({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <form>{children}</form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerInput() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { update },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta: { inputRef },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<TextInput
M|vercel-composition-patterns|ref={inputRef}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|value={state.input}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|onChangeText={(text) => update((s) => ({ ...s, input: text }))}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerSubmit() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { submit },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <Button onPress={submit}>Send</Button>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Export as compound component
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const Composer = {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Provider: ComposerProvider,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Frame: ComposerFrame,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Input: ComposerInput,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Submit: ComposerSubmit,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Header: ComposerHeader,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Footer: ComposerFooter,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Attachments: ComposerAttachments,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Formatting: ComposerFormatting,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Emojis: ComposerEmojis,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Usage:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Provider state={state} actions={actions} meta={meta}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Header />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Provider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Consumers explicitly compose exactly what they need. No hidden conditionals. And the state, actions and meta are dependency-injected by a parent provider, allowing multiple usages of the same componen
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Patterns for lifting state and managing shared ctx across
M|vercel-composition-patterns|composed components.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM (enables swapping state implementations without changing UI)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The provider component should be the only place that knows how state is managed.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|UI components consume the ctx interface—they don't know if state comes from
M|vercel-composition-patterns|useState, Zustand, or a server sync.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: UI coupled to state implementation**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// UI component knows about global state implementation
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const state = useGlobalChannelState(channelId)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { submit, updateInput } = useChannelSync(channelId)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input
M|vercel-composition-patterns|value={state.input}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|onChange={(text) => sync.updateInput(text)}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit onPress={() => sync.submit()} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: state management isolated in provider**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Provider handles all state management details
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelProvider({
M|vercel-composition-patterns|channelId,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|children,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}: {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|channelId: string
M|vercel-composition-patterns|children: React.ReactNode
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { state, update, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Provider
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state={state}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions={{ update, submit }}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Provider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// UI component only knows about the ctx interface
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelComposer() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Header />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Usage
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function Channel({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ChannelProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ChannelComposer />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ChannelProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Different providers, same UI:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Local state for ephemeral forms
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageProvider({ children }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Provider
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state={state}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions={{ update: setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Provider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Global synced state for channels
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelProvider({ channelId, children }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { state, update, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Provider state={state} actions={{ update, submit }}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Provider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The same `Composer.Input` component works with both providers because it only
M|vercel-composition-patterns|depends on the ctx interface, not the implementation.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: HIGH (enables dependency-injectable state across use-cases)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Define a **generic interface** for your component ctx with three parts:
M|vercel-composition-patterns|`state`, `actions`, and `meta`. This interface is a contract that any provider
M|vercel-composition-patterns|can implement—enabling the same UI components to work with completely different
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state implementations.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Core principle:** Lift state, compose internals, make state
M|vercel-composition-patterns|dependency-injectable.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: UI coupled to specific state implementation**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerInput() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Tightly coupled to a specific hook
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { input, setInput } = useChannelComposerState()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <TextInput value={input} onChangeText={setInput} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: generic interface enables dependency injection**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Define a GENERIC interface that any provider can implement
M|vercel-composition-patterns|interface ComposerState {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|input: string
M|vercel-composition-patterns|attachments: Attachment[]
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isSubmitting: boolean
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|interface ComposerActions {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|update: (updater: (state: ComposerState) => ComposerState) => void
M|vercel-composition-patterns|submit: () => void
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|interface ComposerMeta {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|inputRef: React.RefObject<TextInput>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|interface ComposerContextValue {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state: ComposerState
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: ComposerActions
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta: ComposerMeta
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue | null>(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**UI components consume the interface, not the implementation:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerInput() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { update },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// This component works with ANY provider that implements the interface
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<TextInput
M|vercel-composition-patterns|ref={meta.inputRef}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|value={state.input}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|onChangeText={(text) => update((s) => ({ ...s, input: text }))}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Different providers implement the same interface:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Provider A: Local state for ephemeral forms
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const submit = useForwardMessage()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ComposerContext
M|vercel-composition-patterns|value={{
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { update: setState, submit },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta: { inputRef },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ComposerContext>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Provider B: Global synced state for channels
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ChannelProvider({ channelId, children }: Props) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { state, update, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ComposerContext
M|vercel-composition-patterns|value={{
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { update, submit },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta: { inputRef },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ComposerContext>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**The same composed UI works with both:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Works with ForwardMessageProvider (local state)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Works with ChannelProvider (global synced state)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ChannelProvider channelId="abc">
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ChannelProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Custom UI outside the component can access state and actions:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{/* The composer UI */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{/* Custom UI OUTSIDE the composer, but INSIDE the provider */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<MessagePreview />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{/* Actions at the bottom of the dialog */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<CancelButton />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardButton />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// This button lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can still submit based on its ctx!
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardButton() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions: { submit },
M|vercel-composition-patterns|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <Button onPress={submit}>Forward</Button>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// This preview lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can read composer's state!
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function MessagePreview() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { state } = use(ComposerContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <Preview message={state.input} attachments={state.attachments} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The provider boundary is what matters—not the visual nesting. Components that
M|vercel-composition-patterns|need shared state don't have to be inside the `Composer.Frame`. They just need
M|vercel-composition-patterns|to be within the provider.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The `ForwardButton` and `MessagePreview` are not visually inside the composer
M|vercel-composition-patterns|box, but they can still access its state and actions. This is the power of
M|vercel-composition-patterns|lifting state into providers.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The UI is reusable bits you compose together. The state is dependency-injected
M|vercel-composition-patterns|by the provider. Swap the provider, keep the UI.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: HIGH (enables state sharing outside component boundaries)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Move state management into dedicated provider components. This allows sibling
M|vercel-composition-patterns|components outside the main UI to access and modify state without prop drilling
M|vercel-composition-patterns|or awkward refs.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: state trapped inside component**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageComposer() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Problem: How does this button access composer state?
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<MessagePreview /> {/* Needs composer state */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<CancelButton />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardButton /> {/* Needs to call submit */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: useEffect to sync state up**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [input, setInput] = useState('')
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageComposer onInputChange={setInput} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<MessagePreview input={input} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageComposer({ onInputChange }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|useEffect(() => {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|onInputChange(state.input) // Sync on every change 😬
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}, [state.input])
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: reading state from ref on submit**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const stateRef = useRef(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageComposer stateRef={stateRef} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardButton onPress={() => submit(stateRef.current)} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: state lifted to provider**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Provider
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state={state}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|actions={{ update: setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{children}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Provider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<MessagePreview /> {/* Custom components can access state and actions */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<CancelButton />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardButton /> {/* Custom components can access state and actions */}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</DialogActions>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Dialog>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardButton() {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const { actions } = use(Composer.ctx)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <Button onPress={actions.submit}>Forward</Button>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|The ForwardButton lives outside the Composer.Frame but still has access to the
M|vercel-composition-patterns|submit action because it's within the provider. Even though it's a one-off
M|vercel-composition-patterns|component, it can still access the composer's state and actions from outside the
M|vercel-composition-patterns|UI itself.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Key insight:** Components that need shared state don't have to be visually
M|vercel-composition-patterns|nested inside each other—they just need to be within the same provider.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Specific techniques for implementing compound components and
M|vercel-composition-patterns|ctx providers.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM (self-documenting code, no hidden conditionals)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Instead of one component with many boolean props, create explicit variant
M|vercel-composition-patterns|components. Each variant composes the pieces it needs. The code documents
M|vercel-composition-patterns|itself.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: one component, many modes**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// What does this component actually render?
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isThread
M|vercel-composition-patterns|isEditing={false}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|channelId='abc'
M|vercel-composition-patterns|showAttachments
M|vercel-composition-patterns|showFormatting={false}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: explicit variants**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Immediately clear what this renders
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ThreadComposer channelId="abc" />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Or
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<EditMessageComposer messageId="xyz" />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Or
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageComposer messageId="123" />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Each implementation is unique, explicit and self-contained. Yet they can each
M|vercel-composition-patterns|use shared parts.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Implementation:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ThreadComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ThreadProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<AlsoSendToChannelField channelId={channelId} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Submit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ThreadProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function EditMessageComposer({ messageId }: { messageId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<EditMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</EditMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ForwardMessageComposer({ messageId }: { messageId: string }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<ForwardMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Mentions />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Each variant is explicit about:
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- What provider/state it uses
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- What UI elements it includes
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- What actions are available
M|vercel-composition-patterns|No boolean prop combinations to reason about. No impossible states.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM (cleaner composition, better readability)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Use `children` for composition instead of `renderX` props. Children are more
M|vercel-composition-patterns|readable, compose naturally, and don't require understanding callback
M|vercel-composition-patterns|signatures.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: render props**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function Composer({
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderHeader,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderFooter,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderActions,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}: {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderHeader?: () => React.ReactNode
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderFooter?: () => React.ReactNode
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderActions?: () => React.ReactNode
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderHeader?.()}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderFooter ? renderFooter() : <DefaultFooter />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|{renderActions?.()}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Usage is awkward and inflexible
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderHeader={() => <CustomHeader />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderFooter={() => (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderActions={() => <SubmitButton />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: compound components with children**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerFrame({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <form>{children}</form>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerFooter({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <footer className='flex'>{children}</footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Usage is flexible
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return (
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<CustomHeader />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Input />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Formatting />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<Composer.Emojis />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<SubmitButton />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Footer>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|</Composer.Frame>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**When render props are appropriate:**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|// Render props work well when you need to pass data back
M|vercel-composition-patterns|<List
M|vercel-composition-patterns|data={items}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|renderItem={({ item, index }) => <Item item={item} index={index} />}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|/>
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Use render props when the parent needs to provide data or state to the child.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Use children when composing static structure.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|React 19+ only. Don't use `forwardRef`; use `use()` instead of `useContext()`.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Impact: MEDIUM (cleaner component definitions and ctx usage)**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|> **⚠️ React 19+ only.** Skip this if you're on React 18 or earlier.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|In React 19, `ref` is now a regular prop (no `forwardRef` wrapper needed), and `use()` replaces `useContext()`.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: forwardRef in React 19**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const ComposerInput = forwardRef<TextInput, Props>((props, ref) => {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|})
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: ref as a regular prop**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|function ComposerInput({ ref, ...props }: Props & { ref?: React.Ref<TextInput> }) {
M|vercel-composition-patterns|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|vercel-composition-patterns|}
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Incorrect: useContext in React 19**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const value = useContext(MyContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|**Correct: use instead of useContext**
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```tsx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|const value = use(MyContext)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|`use()` can also be called conditionally, unlike `useContext()`.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|1. [https://react.dev](https://react.dev)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|2. [https://react.dev/learn/passing-data-deeply-with-ctx](https://react.dev/learn/passing-data-deeply-with-ctx)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|3. [https://react.dev/reference/react/use](https://react.dev/reference/react/use)